Gnomish Thug <BR>
Defiant</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usanitylost.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sanity Lost</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/29/01 12:31:46 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Pickpocketing in PvP !</span><hr size=1> It was in beta, and also was in early release. You could pickpocket any level person, and the level had no relation to skill on players. It was totally unbalanced and it was a bitch to non-rogues.<br>
<br>
IT IS NOT COMING BACK. <p><font color="red"><font size=1>This world's a crazy place... or maybe it's just me.</font></font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucircilly.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Circilly</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/29/01 3:29:58 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Pickpocketing in PvP !</span><hr size=1> Well if you had bothered to read it even you'd notice that I asked for rather simple restrictions on it.  I mean heck they fixed disarm rather just nerfing it from PvP, its not that incredibly hard to put in a few codes to only allow it on people in PvP range or max amounts per lvl etc.  And no, its not coming back if no one cares, and if even fellow rogues don't care then I doubt anyone else would. <p>Circilly <BR>
Gnomish Thug <BR>
Defiant</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usanitylost.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sanity Lost</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/29/01 10:21:18 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Pickpocketing in PvP !</span><hr size=1> Sorry, internet was being a bitch that night and wouldn't open the page, so you're right, I didn't read it.<br>
<br>
Still think it's a bad idea... I mean, c'mon, buying a mrylokar's suit and jacking back half the cash you paid?<br>
<br>
No thanks, UO was bad enough with that. <p><font color="red"><font size=1>This world's a crazy place... or maybe it's just me.</font></font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ushariin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shariin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/1/01 11:17:43 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Pickpocketing in PvP !</span><hr size=1> As opposed to buying a Mry suit and then just waxing the guy and *taking* the money back?  How the heck anybody could afford a full suit at once is way beyond me, but the point stands.<br>
<br>
There are *already* ways to get coin from people.  This is just a bit faster, a bit less risky, and much less profitable. <p><style type="text/css">
