 <p>"Come on, turn around... turn around... BACKSTAB!!"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ufreonsmurf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>FreonSmurf</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC= http://hoels76.tripod.com/u093.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/2/01 6:51:08 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://hoels76.tripod.com/wee.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Pickpocketing in PvP !</span><hr size=1> <b>1) Only usable on players who you can PvP with of course, you can't disarm someone out of PvP range for example on a PvP server and this should be the same.<br>
</b><br>
Within the level limits only makes sense, sounds good so far.<br>
<b>2) Notification of the crime, it could be as vague as "your purse feels lighter" to "Soandso has stolen such and such amount from you"<br>
</b><br>
Ok your taking a huge leap of faith and assuming Verant could easily add pickpocket in the code to take from a PC loot pool without having any exploitable features or bugs. This game has been out almost 2 years, no pickpocket in PVP or any metion of trying it.  Your not the first person to ask for this, wont be the last either, but understand somewhere over the rainbow, there sits a person at Verant who doesnt give a damn about PVP servers let alone adding pickpocket to the game for PVP.<br>
<br>
<b>3) Reasonable limits on the skill, for example a max pickpocket of 5 gold per lvl per attempt assuming the other skill checks didnt fail. Perhaps only able to pickpocket copper until lvl 10, and only silver until lvl 20. I'm sure the many rogues in Norrath could fill in many other possible ideas, which would utterly defeat someone merely sitting at a bank to pickpocket while naked and still allow for fun and enjoyment of the skill.</b><br>
Small amount of money doesnt matter skill can be easily exploited. Factions hits or guard agro must be invovled. Pickpocket has  a chance to steal items as well, as we all know for Verant to make simple changes in the game takes a long time, and to seprate coin from npc loot pool isnt something "easy" for them to do.<br>
<br>
There are so many issue that directly effect the rogue class ,getting a little more pocket change is not gonna effect it one bit. How many people do ya know above level 20 that exp and dont have see invis up?<br>
<br>
Past level 35? Please gimme a break every damn inkie has dmf and everydamn light damn well has see invis up anywhere they are walking around with loot.<br>
<br>
Level 46? Better loot ganking people at zone lines or something than trying to sneak up a group in Dreadlands or Overthere to steal a few plat.<br>
<br>
Verant is not one to do a massive engine revamp for something as trivial as pickpocket for rogues. <br>
<br>
<b> Since a rogue would still be able to make more money by simply killing the person targeted and looting all coin in the time it would take to continually pickpocket them, this form of combat would remain a fun addition to the class with NO harmful side effects assuming the proper coding restrictions were put in place. </b><br>
ROFL, buddy this screams exploit like a wild turkey running around in Novemeber.<br>
<br>
<b>If others have suggestions or ideas for how to implement this, please voice them and let Verant know of your interest in improving the rogue class in PvP with something that was tossed aside long ago as unbalanced.</b> <br>
Thats right, it is unbalanced and will never happen.  All the hard work to kill someone just for a faction hit and some coin? Sure rogues can skip all that and just steal the loot?<br>
<br>
www.shadowbane.com<br>
www.horizons.com<br>
www.anarachyonline.com<br>
<br>
This is where ya wanna look if ya yearn to play a rogue the way it should be.<br>
<br>
<br>
hate to burst ya bubble, but ya could use your enegry doing stuff like sitting down and building up gas in your small intestine, and releasing it with colorful phrases like" Did you see that barking mouse!!"<br>
<br>
In short,pickpocket in anyform will never been seen in PVP. <p><P><center><font face ="Verdana,Arial" size="3" color="red">
